The paper deals with channel coding and decoding, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of bins and partitioning suggests that the paper may also be relevant to coding theory (cs.CC) and statistical learning (cs.SI). The analysis of exact random coding error exponents involves probability and statistics, which could place the paper in the data structures (cs.DS) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
